-- Embraer Considers Building Ships to Supply to Brazil’s Navy
-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 2012-11-10T16:13:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-10/embraer-considers-building-ships-to-supply-to-brazil-s-navy.html
Embraer SA, the world’s fourth-
largest planemaker, is considering building ships to sell to the
Brazilian navy.  The company is considering entering the shipyard business
through its defense unit, a company press official, who can’t be
identified under corporate policy, said in a telephone
interview, confirming information published today in Rio de
Janeiro-based newspaper  O Globo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in Rio de Janeiro at 
